	  <history>
	    <origin>
	      <origPlace>
		<placeName key="pl:Sannati">Sannati</placeName>,
		built into the wall of the Durgā temple. However,
		according to <ref target="bibl:Sarma1993">Sarma
		and Varaprasada Rao 1993</ref>, this was found
		near the ruined stūpa site (<placeName
		key="pl:SAN-4">SAN-4</placeName>) near the Durgā
		temple. It seems, however, that the editors mistakenly
		combined the find-spots for items no. 223 and 224
		in ARIE 1966–1967.
	      </origPlace>
	      <origDate
		  notBefore-custom="0100"
		  notAfter-custom="0200"
		  precision="medium"
		  evidence="nomenclature">2nd c. CE</origDate>
	    </origin>
	    <provenance when="2016">Current location unknown (possibly still in the Durgā temple?).</provenance>
	  </history>
	</msDesc>
