      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:Sarma1993">Sarma and Varaprasada Rao 1993</ref>, slightly revised by me (AO).</p>
	<p><foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">ūmārasa</foreign> is probably an engraver’s mistake for <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">kumārasa</foreign>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  muḍāna mahāgāmi-<app><lem 
	    source="#ARIE1966">ū</lem><rdg 
	    source="#Sarma1993">ku</rdg><rdg
	    source="#NagarajaRao1985">u</rdg></app><lb n="2" break="no"/>
	  mārasa
	  <persName key="pers:Sa-Otika"><app><lem
            source="#NagarajaRao1985"><unclear>o</unclear></lem><rdg 
	    source="#ARIE1966 #Sarma1993">de</rdg></app><app><lem
	    source="#ARIE1966">ti</lem><rdg
	    source="#Sarma1993">ṭi</rdg></app>kasa</persName>
	  <lb n="3"/>
	  bhaṭi-bālakāya
	  <lb n="4"/>
	  <placeName key="pl:Ahimarikā">a<app><lem>ha</lem><rdg 
	    source="#ARIE1966 #Sarma1993">hi</rdg></app>marikāya</placeName>
	  <lb n="5"/>
	  <persName key="pers:Sa-Puruṣadattā">purisadatāya</persName>
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation">
	<p>
	  Of <persName key="pers:Sa-Puruṣadattā">Puruṣadattā</persName>
	  of <placeName key="pl:Ahimarikā">Ahimarikā</placeName>,
	  the bhaṭṭi-bālakā (eldest daughter?) of
	  <persName key="pers:Sa-Otika">Otika</persName>,
	  the Mahāgrāmikumāra of the Muḍas.
	</p>
      </div>
